---
description: Standardize service method naming and request-response shapes
globs: firebase/functions/src/Services/**/*Service.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Service Method Shape Conventions

- Keep service files class-based with a singleton export (`export const projectService = new ProjectService()`).
- Keep public service methods request-object based; avoid positional argument APIs.
- Naming semantics:
  - `getEntityByIdOrThrow(request)` => one record or `RpcError("NOT_FOUND", ...)`
  - `listEntities(request)` => paginated/filterable `{ nodes, pageInfo }`
  - `createEntity(request)` / `updateEntity(request)` => zod-validate, write, return the row
  - `orderedBatchLoadByIds(ids)` => dataloader backend, results ordered to match input ids
- Use the shared data helpers (`listRows`, `getRowByIdOrThrow`, `idempotentInsertAndGet` from `firebase/functions/src/Data/Utils`) instead of ad-hoc query shapes.
- Method body shape: parse/validate -> DB ops -> typed return -> expected `RpcError`.
- Define exported request/response/field types at the bottom of the file.
- Exemplars: `firebase/functions/src/Services/Identity/UserService.ts`, `firebase/functions/src/Services/Project/ProjectService.ts`.

## Avoid

- One-off `fetch*`/`query*` method names for standard get/list patterns.
- Returning untyped object blobs from public service methods.
